@carmstrong, @egbertp, yes, this same change is also in #3679.

@bacongobbler I'd put a lot of thought into the security ramifications of this (because @carmstrong had raised them to me once before).   Unless I am missing something, I don't believe they're quite as dire as they appear on the surface...

This would grant additional environmental context to Fleet / systemd when they _start_ the unit.  Unless the unit explicitly passes any of that context to the Docker container with `-e` flags (which it does not), I don't believe that any application gains any new awareness of the host environment.

I have actually put this to the test as well... I am running a custom build of Deis currently that already includes this change (from #3679).  I can `nse` to an application container and verify that the variables I normally poke into `/etc/environment` are inaccessible.

